Q10.Write a PHP script to generate an XML file in the following format in PHP.
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<BookInfo>
<book>
<bookno>1</bookno>
<bookname>JAVA</bookname>
<authorname> Balguru Swami</authorname>
<price>250</price>
<year>2006</year>
</book>
<book>
<bookno>2</bookno>
<bookname>C</bookname>
<authorname> Denis Ritchie</authorname>
<price>500</price>
<year>1971</year>
</book>
</BookInfo>


Answer:::::::::
<?php
$str = <<<XML
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<BookInfo>
	<book>
		<bookno>1</bookno>
		<bookname>Java</bookname>
		<authorname>abc</authorname>
		<price>200</price>
		<year>2006</year>
	</book>
	<book>
		<bookno>2</bookno>
		<bookname>Python</bookname>
		<authorname>xyz</authorname>
		<price>300</price>
		<year>2009</year>
	</book>
</BookInfo>
XML;

$fname = "BookInfo.xml";
$f = fopen($fname,"w");
fwrite($f,$str);
fclose($f);

echo "success ".$fname;
?>
